The paper discusses the Iteratively Reweighted Least Squares (IRLS) algorithm, which is commonly used in signal processing and sparse recovery. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the dynamics of a slime mold, which is a biological system, indicating that cs.DS (Dynamical Systems) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses convergence and complexity bounds, which suggests that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible sub-categories.
